# SOLP Vision

## Sudanese Open Language Project

### Vision

The Sudanese Open Language Project (SOLP) envisions a future where every language spoken in Sudan has a strong digital presence and the resources needed to thrive in the modern world.

Beginning with Sudanese Arabic, SOLP aims to build the digital infrastructure that preserves, documents, and empowers the languages of Sudan through open, high-quality language resources.

The project seeks to ensure that Sudanese languages are represented in education, scientific research, software development, language learning, and artificial intelligence.

Rather than building a single application or AI model, SOLP focuses on creating the foundational resources upon which dictionaries, translation systems, educational platforms, speech technologies, OCR systems, natural language processing tools, and future AI applications can be built.

SOLP is a long-term, community-driven initiative that welcomes collaboration from linguists, researchers, developers, students, educators, and native speakers from across Sudan.

By combining scientific standards with open collaboration, SOLP aims to become the leading open reference for Sudanese language resources while preserving Sudan's rich linguistic and cultural heritage for future generations.


## Long-Term Vision

Over time, SOLP will expand beyond Sudanese Arabic to include all languages spoken in Sudan, providing open digital resources that preserve linguistic diversity and enable future technological innovation.


## Core Principles

- Open Source
- Scientific Accuracy
- Community Collaboration
- Transparency
- Inclusiveness
- Cultural Preservation
- Long-Term Sustainability
  

## Vision Statement

Building the digital infrastructure for Sudanese Arabic and, ultimately, all languages of Sudan.
